00:04:31.655 --> 00:04:33.770 align:middle line:90%
It was made only in 1991.

00:04:33.770 --> 00:04:37.490 align:middle line:84%
It's a discovery that
involves the human heart.

00:04:37.490 --> 00:04:41.900 align:middle line:84%
Now this is interesting
unto itself because we--

00:04:41.900 --> 00:04:46.280 align:middle line:84%
our society-- have been
doing heart transplants

00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:50.060 align:middle line:84%
from one human to
another since the 1960s,

00:04:50.060 --> 00:04:52.700 align:middle line:84%
and they have been
relatively successful.

00:04:52.700 --> 00:04:55.220 align:middle line:84%
They don't happen
necessarily every day,

00:04:55.220 --> 00:04:56.720 align:middle line:84%
but there are an
average of maybe

00:04:56.720 --> 00:05:00.020 align:middle line:84%
5,000 heart transplants
per year in the world,

00:05:00.020 --> 00:05:02.630 align:middle line:84%
and they are
relatively successful.

00:05:02.630 --> 00:05:07.220 align:middle line:84%
And scientists attribute
that success to their belief

00:05:07.220 --> 00:05:09.110 align:middle line:84%
that we pretty much
know everything there

00:05:09.110 --> 00:05:11.150 align:middle line:90%
is to know about the heart.

00:05:11.150 --> 00:05:13.820 align:middle line:84%
And it's for that reason
that a discovery--

00:05:13.820 --> 00:05:15.980 align:middle line:84%
such as the one I'm
about to share with you,

00:05:15.980 --> 00:05:19.340 align:middle line:90%
made relatively late in 1991--

00:05:19.340 --> 00:05:20.540 align:middle line:90%
is now on the radar.

00:05:20.540 --> 00:05:23.840 align:middle line:84%
How could we have gone so
long without recognizing what

00:05:23.840 --> 00:05:26.180 align:middle line:90%
this discovery is telling us?

00:05:26.180 --> 00:05:29.670 align:middle line:84%
Well, the discovery itself
is that scientists now

00:05:29.670 --> 00:05:33.450 align:middle line:84%
recognize we have
within our hearts

00:05:33.450 --> 00:05:39.600 align:middle line:84%
about 40,000 specialized
cells concentrated

00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:42.520 align:middle line:84%
in a very precise
way in our hearts.

00:05:42.520 --> 00:05:46.650 align:middle line:84%
The specialized cells, they
are called sensory neurites.

00:05:46.650 --> 00:05:49.890 align:middle line:84%
Sensory neurites, that's
a very technical term.

00:05:49.890 --> 00:05:52.500 align:middle line:84%
It means they're essentially
brain-like cells,

00:05:52.500 --> 00:05:53.910 align:middle line:90%
but they're not in our brain.

00:05:53.910 --> 00:05:55.550 align:middle line:90%
They're in our heart.

00:05:55.550 --> 00:05:59.790 align:middle line:84%
And that they are in our heart,
concentrated in such a way,

00:05:59.790 --> 00:06:03.660 align:middle line:84%
that scientists now call
these cells in our heart

00:06:03.660 --> 00:06:06.820 align:middle line:90%
the little brain in the heart.

00:06:06.820 --> 00:06:08.700 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that
is so amazing to me

00:06:08.700 --> 00:06:12.240 align:middle line:84%
is the name of the man
who found the cells.

00:06:12.240 --> 00:06:14.024 align:middle line:90%
His last name's Armour.

00:06:14.024 --> 00:06:17.520 align:middle line:90%
Armour-- this is love in French.

00:06:17.520 --> 00:06:21.120 align:middle line:84%
So when I think
about karmic destiny

00:06:21.120 --> 00:06:22.919 align:middle line:84%
and maybe what this
man's karma was--

00:06:22.919 --> 00:06:24.960 align:middle line:84%
at the age of five years
old if someone asked him

00:06:24.960 --> 00:06:26.460 align:middle line:84%
what he was going to do
for a living he would say,

00:06:26.460 --> 00:06:28.168 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to make a
discovery of a heart.

00:06:28.168 --> 00:06:29.490 align:middle line:90%
It's in my name.

00:06:29.490 --> 00:06:33.930 align:middle line:84%
But this kind of
discovery is so powerful.

00:06:33.930 --> 00:06:37.590 align:middle line:84%
And what it is that he found--
these 40,000 cells in the human

00:06:37.590 --> 00:06:38.490 align:middle line:90%
heart--

00:06:38.490 --> 00:06:40.480 align:middle line:90%
because this isn't a metaphor.

00:06:40.480 --> 00:06:41.580 align:middle line:90%
This is literal.

00:06:41.580 --> 00:06:46.950 align:middle line:84%
These cells in our heart,
they learn independently

00:06:46.950 --> 00:06:50.880 align:middle line:84%
of cells in our brain, of
the neurons in our brain.

00:06:50.880 --> 00:06:55.230 align:middle line:84%
They think independently
of the cells in our brain.

00:06:55.230 --> 00:06:59.890 align:middle line:84%
They feel independently
of the cells in our brain.

00:06:59.890 --> 00:07:02.310 align:middle line:84%
So what we're finding
now is that we

00:07:02.310 --> 00:07:06.660 align:middle line:84%
have a form of intelligence
focused in the heart that

00:07:06.660 --> 00:07:10.140 align:middle line:84%
can function completely
separately from what

00:07:10.140 --> 00:07:12.030 align:middle line:90%
we typically know in the brain.

00:07:12.030 --> 00:07:15.150 align:middle line:84%
And as you'll see in a moment,
they can also be married.

00:07:15.150 --> 00:07:18.340 align:middle line:84%
They can be harmonized
with the human brain.

00:07:18.340 --> 00:07:21.150 align:middle line:84%
The heart and the brain may be
harmonized in a very precise

00:07:21.150 --> 00:07:23.070 align:middle line:90%
way to awaken these functions.

00:07:23.070 --> 00:07:25.170 align:middle line:84%
Before we get into
that, I just want

00:07:25.170 --> 00:07:27.990 align:middle line:84%
to share with you
some examples of how

00:07:27.990 --> 00:07:32.630 align:middle line:84%
real these cells and
their function really are.

00:07:32.630 --> 00:07:35.740 align:middle line:84%
It is very common for medical
doctors and scientists--

00:07:35.740 --> 00:07:37.710 align:middle line:84%
they would go to
conferences and they

00:07:37.710 --> 00:07:40.020 align:middle line:84%
would share with other
scientists and researchers

00:07:40.020 --> 00:07:42.990 align:middle line:84%
and doctors their experiences
in heart research,

00:07:42.990 --> 00:07:46.200 align:middle line:84%
or for the doctors
sometimes, heart transplants.

00:07:46.200 --> 00:07:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And it was common
for stories to arise

00:07:50.580 --> 00:07:54.780 align:middle line:84%
where a recipient
of a heart would--

00:07:54.780 --> 00:07:59.490 align:middle line:84%
a successful recipient of a
heart would begin to assume

00:07:59.490 --> 00:08:01.620 align:middle line:84%
different characteristics
of personality

00:08:01.620 --> 00:08:04.320 align:middle line:84%
and different qualities
of the way they thought

00:08:04.320 --> 00:08:06.630 align:middle line:84%
about themselves and
viewed life after the heart

00:08:06.630 --> 00:08:10.590 align:middle line:84%
transplant from what they had
before the heart transplant.

00:08:10.590 --> 00:08:12.420 align:middle line:84%
So one of the first
stories, for example,

00:08:12.420 --> 00:08:15.990 align:middle line:84%
it was a woman that
received the heart--

00:08:15.990 --> 00:08:20.820 align:middle line:84%
she knew it was from a male, and
typically the donor information

00:08:20.820 --> 00:08:22.800 align:middle line:84%
is not shared with
the recipient.

00:08:22.800 --> 00:08:26.580 align:middle line:84%
Typically, that information
is sealed in the courts.

00:08:26.580 --> 00:08:27.690 align:middle line:90%
It can be discovered.

00:08:27.690 --> 00:08:29.900 align:middle line:84%
And there are ways to
do it, as you'll see,

00:08:29.900 --> 00:08:32.260 align:middle line:90%
but it's not commonly done.

00:08:32.260 --> 00:08:35.309 align:middle line:84%
So the woman's transplant
was successful.

00:08:35.309 --> 00:08:37.289 align:middle line:84%
And when the doctor
came to check on her

00:08:37.289 --> 00:08:39.960 align:middle line:84%
and he asked her the question,
he said, how do you feel?

00:08:39.960 --> 00:08:41.470 align:middle line:90%
She said, I feel fine.

00:08:41.470 --> 00:08:42.270 align:middle line:90%
I feel great.

00:08:42.270 --> 00:08:43.706 align:middle line:90%
She says, I'm hungry.

00:08:43.706 --> 00:08:46.080 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor said, OK, I'll
have the hospital bring you

00:08:46.080 --> 00:08:47.550 align:middle line:90%
some food.

00:08:47.550 --> 00:08:49.460 align:middle line:84%
And she immediately--
she recoiled.

00:08:49.460 --> 00:08:51.600 align:middle line:84%
She says, I don't
want hospital food.

00:08:51.600 --> 00:08:55.830 align:middle line:84%
She had very specific kinds of
food that she was asking for.

00:08:55.830 --> 00:08:57.600 align:middle line:84%
And what makes
this interesting is

00:08:57.600 --> 00:09:00.300 align:middle line:84%
that there were types of
food that she had never

00:09:00.300 --> 00:09:05.100 align:middle line:84%
eaten in her life before
she received this heart.

00:09:05.100 --> 00:09:06.900 align:middle line:84%
Very specific kinds
of food, and there

00:09:06.900 --> 00:09:09.670 align:middle line:84%
was only one place where
this food could be found,

00:09:09.670 --> 00:09:13.260 align:middle line:84%
and that is at a fast food
restaurant that is called KFC.

00:09:13.260 --> 00:09:16.950 align:middle line:84%
KFC is the only food that
would satisfy the cravings

00:09:16.950 --> 00:09:18.270 align:middle line:90%
that she was having.

00:09:18.270 --> 00:09:22.020 align:middle line:84%
Well after she was
released from the hospital,

00:09:22.020 --> 00:09:24.645 align:middle line:84%
she wanted to find out
whose heart she had.

00:09:24.645 --> 00:09:26.145 align:middle line:84%
The records were
sealed, but she did

00:09:26.145 --> 00:09:27.990 align:middle line:84%
a little personal
investigative work,

00:09:27.990 --> 00:09:29.790 align:middle line:84%
and she went through
some obituary columns.

00:09:29.790 --> 00:09:31.140 align:middle line:90%
It was a small town.

00:09:31.140 --> 00:09:35.340 align:middle line:84%
She was able to go
back, and she found

00:09:35.340 --> 00:09:37.950 align:middle line:84%
that the heart she
had received was

00:09:37.950 --> 00:09:42.060 align:middle line:84%
from a man who had died
in a motorcycle accident.

00:09:42.060 --> 00:09:44.710 align:middle line:84%
And she was able to track
down-- through the obituary--

00:09:44.710 --> 00:09:48.750 align:middle line:84%
his family, his parents, and
go to talk to them to find out

00:09:48.750 --> 00:09:52.170 align:middle line:84%
about the man's life whose
heart was now in her body.

00:09:52.170 --> 00:09:55.020 align:middle line:84%
And during that
conversation what she found

00:09:55.020 --> 00:09:58.140 align:middle line:84%
is this man's
favorite diet was KFC.

00:09:58.140 --> 00:10:01.380 align:middle line:84%
And when doctors hear
things like that they say,

00:10:01.380 --> 00:10:04.320 align:middle line:90%
huh, isn't that a coincidence.

00:10:04.320 --> 00:10:05.910 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that interesting?

00:10:05.910 --> 00:10:08.160 align:middle line:84%
And then they go on to
the next transplant.

00:10:08.160 --> 00:10:10.740 align:middle line:84%
Well this has happened
time and time again

00:10:10.740 --> 00:10:13.710 align:middle line:84%
and it has been written
off as anecdotal,

00:10:13.710 --> 00:10:19.260 align:middle line:84%
that is until one particular
story changed everything.

00:10:19.260 --> 00:10:24.180 align:middle line:84%
This is a story that happened
in a small town in the Midwest.

00:10:24.180 --> 00:10:28.050 align:middle line:84%
It was a story of
an 8-year-old girl

00:10:28.050 --> 00:10:31.940 align:middle line:84%
who received the heart of
another little girl who

00:10:31.940 --> 00:10:35.490 align:middle line:84%
was only two years older,
a 10-year-old girl.

00:10:35.490 --> 00:10:38.930 align:middle line:84%
And the heart transplant
was successful.

00:10:38.930 --> 00:10:40.430 align:middle line:84%
And typically, this
is what happens.

00:10:40.430 --> 00:10:44.840 align:middle line:84%
The doctors will try to match
the heart from the donor

00:10:44.840 --> 00:10:47.390 align:middle line:84%
to the recipient
within a range of ages

00:10:47.390 --> 00:10:48.890 align:middle line:84%
so that a very
young person isn't

00:10:48.890 --> 00:10:51.850 align:middle line:84%
getting a huge
heart or the older

00:10:51.850 --> 00:10:54.080 align:middle line:90%
heart of a very older person.

00:10:54.080 --> 00:10:56.200 align:middle line:84%
So the young girl, she
received the heart.

00:10:56.200 --> 00:10:58.820 align:middle line:84%
The transplant was
