00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:12.290 align:middle line:84%
the younger girl-- and she was
able to share those memories

00:14:12.290 --> 00:14:13.630 align:middle line:90%
with the authorities.

00:14:13.630 --> 00:14:16.880 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sharing this story
with you for one reason--

00:14:16.880 --> 00:14:20.570 align:middle line:84%
that is how real the
memory is in our hearts.

00:14:20.570 --> 00:14:21.980 align:middle line:90%
It's not a metaphor.

00:14:21.980 --> 00:14:26.390 align:middle line:84%
It is a literal
storage of impressions,

00:14:26.390 --> 00:14:28.990 align:middle line:90%
of memories that we all have.

00:14:28.990 --> 00:14:31.310 align:middle line:84%
But the heart has
its own language.

00:14:31.310 --> 00:14:33.050 align:middle line:84%
The heart speaks
to us in a language

00:14:33.050 --> 00:14:35.150 align:middle line:84%
different than our
mind, and we communicate

00:14:35.150 --> 00:14:38.780 align:middle line:84%
with our heart in a language
very different from our mind.

00:14:38.780 --> 00:14:41.960 align:middle line:84%
So we know now that
these specialized cells,

00:14:41.960 --> 00:14:45.230 align:middle line:84%
these sensory neurites, they
serve three functions-- they

00:14:45.230 --> 00:14:50.120 align:middle line:84%
learn, they remember, and
they think independently

00:14:50.120 --> 00:14:55.670 align:middle line:84%
of the cells in our brain,
and they can also be tuned,

00:14:55.670 --> 00:14:59.499 align:middle line:84%
harmonized, to function together
with the cells in our brain.

00:14:59.499 --> 00:15:01.040 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to
invite you now, think

00:15:01.040 --> 00:15:02.480 align:middle line:90%
about what I'm saying to you.

00:15:02.480 --> 00:15:05.060 align:middle line:84%
Two separate organs--
a heart and a brain--

00:15:05.060 --> 00:15:08.450 align:middle line:84%
but they share an
extended neural network

00:15:08.450 --> 00:15:13.160 align:middle line:84%
that's made possible by
the genetic fusion that

00:15:13.160 --> 00:15:18.090 align:middle line:84%
happened 200,000 plus years
ago that makes us who we are.

00:15:18.090 --> 00:15:19.946 align:middle line:84%
We typically-- in
our culture, we

00:15:19.946 --> 00:15:21.320 align:middle line:84%
are very accustomed
to our brain.

00:15:21.320 --> 00:15:23.750 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes we discount our heart.

00:15:23.750 --> 00:15:25.970 align:middle line:84%
And especially for males
in the Western culture,

00:15:25.970 --> 00:15:29.139 align:middle line:84%
we've been conditioned to
discount the intuition that

00:15:29.139 --> 00:15:30.680 align:middle line:84%
comes from our heart,
and we're going

00:15:30.680 --> 00:15:33.200 align:middle line:90%
to explore in these episodes.

00:15:33.200 --> 00:15:35.030 align:middle line:84%
Other cultures do
just the opposite.

00:15:35.030 --> 00:15:38.030 align:middle line:84%
There are cultures when the
young children are born--

00:15:38.030 --> 00:15:42.020 align:middle line:84%
such as the Kogi, for
example, in South America--

00:15:42.020 --> 00:15:44.120 align:middle line:84%
their emphasis as
young children is

00:15:44.120 --> 00:15:47.510 align:middle line:84%
on developing the thinking,
the feeling, and the memory

00:15:47.510 --> 00:15:50.210 align:middle line:84%
of the heart first
for a period of years,

00:15:50.210 --> 00:15:53.090 align:middle line:84%
and then they are
immersed in the world

00:15:53.090 --> 00:15:55.460 align:middle line:84%
with all of the
physical activity

00:15:55.460 --> 00:15:57.890 align:middle line:90%
to engage their thinking mind.

00:15:57.890 --> 00:16:00.860 align:middle line:10%
But they learn about
the world of their mind

00:16:00.860 --> 00:16:02.510 align:middle line:10%
through their
heart, where we are

00:16:02.510 --> 00:16:04.460 align:middle line:10%
conditioned to learn
about the heart

00:16:04.460 --> 00:16:05.990 align:middle line:10%
through the world of our mind.

00:16:05.990 --> 00:16:07.370 align:middle line:10%
I think it's fascinating.

00:16:07.370 --> 00:16:10.077 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not saying what is
right and wrong, good or bad.

00:16:10.077 --> 00:16:11.660 align:middle line:84%
They're just very,
very different ways

00:16:11.660 --> 00:16:14.040 align:middle line:84%
of embracing the
potential, and that's

00:16:14.040 --> 00:16:15.290 align:middle line:90%
where I'm going with all this.

00:16:15.290 --> 00:16:16.880 align:middle line:84%
This is why I'm
sharing this with you.

00:16:16.880 --> 00:16:21.480 align:middle line:84%
We have this potential, and it's
been with us from the moment

00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:22.280 align:middle line:90%
that we appeared.

00:16:22.280 --> 00:16:24.740 align:middle line:84%
It didn't develop
slowly, gradually

00:16:24.740 --> 00:16:26.120 align:middle line:90%
over long periods of time.

00:16:26.120 --> 00:16:29.090 align:middle line:84%
We are over-endowed
with this potential.

00:16:29.090 --> 00:16:30.420 align:middle line:90%
So, what does that mean?

00:16:30.420 --> 00:16:33.290 align:middle line:84%
What does it mean in our lives
to have this kind of potential?

00:16:33.290 --> 00:16:37.730 align:middle line:84%
Well, when we harmonize our
heart and our brain together,

00:16:37.730 --> 00:16:40.550 align:middle line:84%
that's what gives us
our super abilities.

00:16:40.550 --> 00:16:43.120 align:middle line:84%
We harmonize the
heart and the brain.

00:16:43.120 --> 00:16:45.320 align:middle line:84%
Again, two separate
organs sharing

00:16:45.320 --> 00:16:48.080 align:middle line:90%
a common neural network.

00:16:48.080 --> 00:16:50.630 align:middle line:10%
So the neurites in our heart
and the neurites in our brain,

00:16:50.630 --> 00:16:54.210 align:middle line:10%
all of a sudden we have
access to super information

00:16:54.210 --> 00:16:55.010 align:middle line:10%
processing.

00:16:55.010 --> 00:16:58.100 align:middle line:84%
We can think and solve problems
